<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="485" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,471,441,467]" box="[151,471,441,467]" pageId="6" pageNumber="485">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,471,441,467]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="6" pageNumber="485" reason="1">
<taxonomicName box="[151,471,441,467]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Pseudodendrothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bhatti">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,471,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="485">Pseudodendrothrips bhatti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,511,896]" pageId="6" pageNumber="485">
The characters of female specimens collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[691,736,512,535]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="485">Iran</collectingCountry>
closely conform to the published description of this species by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kudo" box="[151,297,548,573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="485" refString="Kudo, I. (1984) The Japanese Dendrothripini with descriptions of four new species (Thysanoptera, Thripidae). Kontyu, 52 (4), 487 - 505." type="journal article" year="1984">
Kud√¥ (
<number box="[228,289,548,572]" pageId="6" pageNumber="485" value="1984.0">1984</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. However, differences in some characters are as follows: pronotum with 
<number box="[1107,1135,548,572]" pageId="6" pageNumber="485" value="12.0">12</number>
discal setae, with about 
<number box="[1408,1436,548,573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="485" value="35.0">35</number>
lines of sculpture at middle; fore wing with light brown band, paler at base and distally, clavus pale, shaded at apex; fore and mid tibiae not shaded. In this respect, Iranian specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[947,1050,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Pseudodendrothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bhattii">
<emphasis box="[947,1050,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="485">P. bhattii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are very similar to samples from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,246,655,680]" name="Pakistan" pageId="6" pageNumber="485">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Akram" box="[317,545,655,680]" pageId="6" pageNumber="485" refString="Akram, W., Shin, B. S., Hwang, C. Y. &amp; Lee, J. J. (2003) Saltatorial leaf feeding genus Pseudodendrothrips (Terebrantia: Thysanoptera) and its species from Pakistan. Korean Journal of Entomology, 33 (2), 69 - 72. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1748 - 5967.2003. tb 00051. x" type="journal article" year="2003">
Akram 
<emphasis box="[408,464,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="485">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[484,545,656,680]" pageId="6" pageNumber="485" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Mound" box="[570,738,655,680]" pageId="6" pageNumber="485" refString="Mound, L. A. (1999) Saltatorial leaf-feeding Thysanoptera (Thripidae, Dendrothripinae) in Australia and New Caledonia, with newly recorded pests of ferns, figs and mulberries. Australian Journal of Entomology, 38 (4), 257 - 273. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1046 / j. 1440 - 6055.1999.00112. x" type="journal article" year="1999">
Mound (
<number box="[672,730,656,680]" pageId="6" pageNumber="485" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
indicated that 
<taxonomicName box="[923,1030,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Pseudodendrothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bhattii">
<emphasis box="[923,1030,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="485">P. bhattii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be distinguished from the Australian species, 
<emphasis box="[373,457,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="485">P. da rc i</emphasis>
, but did not synonymise these two because of the difference in host plant records; 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Pseudodendrothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bhattii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="485">P. bhattii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been reported only on 
<taxonomicName box="[525,598,729,752]" class="Aves" family="Sulidae" genus="Morus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Suliformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="485" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[525,598,729,752]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="485">Morus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas 
<taxonomicName box="[711,796,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Pseudodendrothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="darci">
<emphasis box="[711,796,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="485">P. darci</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only on 
<taxonomicName box="[894,956,728,751]" class="Gastropoda" family="Ficidae" genus="Ficus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="6" pageNumber="485" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[894,956,728,751]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="485">Ficus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Interestingly, we collected two specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[182,285,764,788]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Pseudodendrothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bhattii">
<emphasis box="[182,285,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="485">P. bhattii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, one from 
<taxonomicName box="[412,474,765,788]" class="Gastropoda" family="Ficidae" genus="Ficus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="6" pageNumber="485" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[412,474,765,788]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="485">Ficus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and another from 
<taxonomicName box="[686,759,765,788]" class="Aves" family="Sulidae" genus="Morus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Suliformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="485" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[686,759,765,788]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="485">Morus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Observation of this species on these two mentioned plants reinforces the suggestion by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mound" box="[473,635,799,824]" pageId="6" pageNumber="485" refString="Mound, L. A. (1999) Saltatorial leaf-feeding Thysanoptera (Thripidae, Dendrothripinae) in Australia and New Caledonia, with newly recorded pests of ferns, figs and mulberries. Australian Journal of Entomology, 38 (4), 257 - 273. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1046 / j. 1440 - 6055.1999.00112. x" type="journal article" year="1999">
Mound (
<number box="[569,627,800,824]" pageId="6" pageNumber="485" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
of synonymy of this species with 
<emphasis box="[1019,1112,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="485">
<taxonomicName box="[1019,1108,800,824]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Pseudodendrothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="darci">P. darci</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
